Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Dena Samantha Robinson in court with attorney Douglas E. Batt.  Randy P. Sitzberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: STW  
Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.   Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing. 

AS TO COUNT 1: The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 36 MONTHS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, with credit for 6 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 18 MONTHS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 18 MONTHS.  

The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation to the State Department of Corrections for a period of 30 MONTHS.  

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
Serve 30 DAYS in the House of Correction STAYED pending agents request. 
The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections and as a condition of probation/ extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.
Restitution in the amount of $2,000.00 payable to Churchill Casualties. 
Provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
No new violations rising to the level of probable cause. 
Cooperate with any other counseling needs to be determined.
Seek and maintain full-time employment.
No contact with Intercontinental Hotel.

The defendant is advised as a convicted felon she may not carry or possess any firearms/body armor.
The defendant is advised that voting rights are suspended during length of sentence.
The defendant is advised of her appeal rights by defense counsel.

FILED: Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief; Pretrial Incarceration Credit; Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement
JusticePoint Pretrial Services Report filed.

Defendant Dena Samantha Robinson in court with attorney Douglas E. Batt.  Randy P. Sitzberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: SES.
Matter scheduled for Plea Hearing. Plea hearing proceeded. Negotiations placed on the record and confirmed by defense counsel and defendant.

The defendant was advised of her Constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Jury Instructions and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting. Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible. 

Court REITERATED condition of bail. Case adjourned for sentencing hearing.
**  Effective August 4, 2018, this calendar will be assigned to Honorable Glenn H. Yamahiro - Branch 34, in Room 313 of the Safety Building.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 17, 2018 at 08:30 am.
